A4a.motivation: To make sure all people have equal access to knowledge. To help ensure that we have a population capable of evaluating opposing arguments and who can think critically on a subject; thereby forming a fact based opinion rather than one informed by propaganda. We cannot accomplish this until the general population has a grasp on basic knowledge, theories and historical events. Higher education teaches people how to think analytically and to discern fact from opinion.
